<div class="demo-home">
  <h1><%= t('demo.welcome') %></h1>
  <p><%= t('demo.description') %></p>

  <div class="features-grid">
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h2><%= t('demo.features.code_coverage') %></h2>
      <p>Track which lines of code are executed in your application. View detailed coverage reports showing runtime vs test coverage.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Real-time runtime coverage collection</li>
        <li>Line-by-line coverage analysis</li>
        <li>Integration with SimpleCov for test coverage</li>
        <li>Web UI for viewing coverage reports</li>
      </ul>
      <%= link_to "View Coverage Report", "/coverage", class: "btn btn-primary", target: "_blank" %>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-card">
      <h2><%= t('demo.features.view_tracking') %></h2>
      <p>Monitor which views and partials are rendered in your Rails application.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Track all rendered views and partials</li>
        <li>Identify unused view templates</li>
        <li>Optimize view rendering performance</li>
        <li>Current status: <strong><%= Coverband.configuration.track_views ? "Enabled" : "Disabled" %></strong></li>
      </ul>
      <%= link_to "Try it: View Posts", posts_path, class: "btn btn-secondary" %>
      <%= link_to "Try it: View Books", books_path, class: "btn btn-secondary" %>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-card">
      <h2><%= t('demo.features.translation_tracking') %></h2>
      <p>Track which I18n translation keys are actually used in your application.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Discover unused translation keys</li>
        <li>Identify missing translations</li>
        <li>Support for multiple locales</li>
        <li>Current status: <strong><%= Coverband.configuration.track_translations ? "Enabled" : "Disabled" %></strong></li>
      </ul>
      <p>This page uses translations! Check the coverage report to see which keys were accessed.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-card">
      <h2><%= t('demo.features.router_tracking') %></h2>
      <p>Monitor which routes in your application are being accessed.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Track route usage patterns</li>
        <li>Identify unused routes</li>
        <li>Optimize routing configuration</li>
        <li>Current status: <strong><%= Coverband.configuration.track_routes ? "Enabled" : "Disabled" %></strong></li>
      </ul>
      <%= link_to "View All Routes", demo_configuration_path, class: "btn btn-secondary" %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="demo-sections">
    <div class="demo-section">
      <h2>Configuration</h2>
      <p>Learn how to configure Coverband and test different storage backends and settings.</p>
      <%= link_to "View Configuration Options", demo_configuration_path, class: "btn btn-primary" %>
    </div>

    <div class="demo-section">
      <h2>Benchmarks</h2>
      <p>Run performance benchmarks to understand Coverband's impact on your application.</p>
      <%= link_to "View Benchmarks", demo_benchmarks_path, class: "btn btn-primary" %>
    </div>

    <div class="demo-section">
      <h2>Memory Profiling</h2>
      <p>Monitor memory usage and understand Coverband's memory footprint.</p>
      <%= link_to "View Memory Stats", demo_profiling_path, class: "btn btn-primary" %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="getting-started">
    <h2>Getting Started with Your App</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Add Coverband to your Gemfile: <code>gem 'coverband'</code></li>
      <li>Run <code>bundle install</code></li>
      <li>Create a configuration file at <code>config/coverband.rb</code></li>
      <li>Mount the web interface in your routes</li>
      <li>Start your app and visit <code>/coverage</code></li>
    </ol>
    <p>For detailed documentation, visit the <%= link_to "Coverband GitHub repository", "https://github.com/danmayer/coverband", target: "_blank" %>.</p>
  </div>
</div>

